# Golden token-baseline hashes for the DEFAULT batch_infer model on THIS device class.
#
# Hash fixtures bind deterministic prompt/output behavior to the executor.
# a small set of (prompt -> greedy-output hash) anchors that pin the token baseline so
# a future kernel/codegen change that SILENTLY shifts bytes is caught by the gate
# instead of by a false cross-worker auto-dock.
#
# Format: <prompt-id> <max-new-tokens> <sha256-hex-of-output-text> <prompt-text>
# algo:   sha256 over the UTF-8 bytes of the decoded, trimmed greedy output string
# model:  llama-3.2-1b-instruct-q4 (Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct Q4_K_M GGUF)
# decode: temperature=0 greedy (argmax), LlamaBackend::generate
#
# SCOPE  -  read docs/DETERMINISM_CLASS.md: these hashes are valid ONLY within a single
# (device, engine, build_hash) verification class. Token-level determinism is
# impossible across heterogeneous Apple Silicon generations,
# so this file pins the baseline for the build that RECORDED it, not for every Mac.
# A mismatch on the SAME class is a real regression (a kernel change shifted bytes);
# a mismatch on a DIFFERENT class is expected and must NOT be read as a regression.
#
# State: SEEDED for class (device_label=metal, engine=candle, build_hash=29788fb25f948522).
# Recorded 2026-06-30 on an Apple M3 Pro (macOS 26.6), candle 0.10.2 + Metal, agent 0.1.0,
# infer_content_id=c9a43b499231c46b. The harness RECORDS missing rows (CX_GOLDEN_RECORD=1)
# and GATES against them otherwise (proven: no-record re-runs passed on build_hash 29788fb25f948522).
# These same hash VALUES were first recorded under build_hash cb257fe8535ef6c7 and re-verified
# green after the rope_dim fallback edit moved build_hash to 29788fb25f948522  -  i.e. the edit is
# byte-identical for the Llama default (only the class LABEL changed, as the content-id intends).
# CAVEAT: device_label is "metal" (coarse, NOT chip-specific), so a DIFFERENT Apple-Silicon
# generation that lands in the same class could legitimately differ. Re-record on each shipped
# reference box; a mismatch is a regression ONLY within the same physical class.
# Record-time greedy outputs: p002 -> "The capital of France is Paris.", p004 -> "2 + 2 = 4".
p001 16 a95d030b2a5c868a6eadaee75d0727dc2af28637e069fbe16f72a67ba42a2787 Once upon a time
p002 16 a1b7eb2ee7a6aded8dda4e6cf30826f5afffb28a5597ee9389e91eb326d4e319 The capital of France is
p003 16 2130651c317ee2f86e59051acd137de3fdfd558106aacc79b7ba8f381e9160dd def quicksort(arr):
p004 16 e93dff0d1076b537cd1bd659d14bb77d5fd47db13204a227cb3cd66e81dd454c 2 + 2 =
